## Notes

- Numbers come from the per-system JSON in `results/`. If a row reads
  `PENDING`, that runner is a v0.1 stub — see the corresponding
  `/destruction/<system>/` page for the locked methodology.
- A row marked `ERROR` means the runner crashed or emitted an
  invalid record. The raw log lives at `logs/<system>.log`.
- The dataset hash is identical across all rows. If hashes diverge
  the comparator aborts before this file is written — we do not
  silently mix apples and oranges.
